This paper discusses the challenges and opportunities presented by the Internet of Things (IoT) and the need for real-time analytics to gain intelligence and respond to events as they happen. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. Additionally, the paper discusses the need to manage and make sense of large amounts of sensor-generated data, which suggests that it could also belong to the Databases (cs.DB) category. The paper also discusses the use of historical analysis and the creation of new and innovative applications, which suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Software Engineering (cs.SE) categories. Finally, the paper discusses the need to optimize equipment and resource usage, which suggests that it could also belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category.
